<p>China said it would retaliate if the United States imposes an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports, after President Trump floated the measure [washingtonpost.com#1][bbc.com#1]. Beijing also accused Washington of &quot;double standards&quot; and said it could introduce &quot;countermeasures&quot; if the tariff goes ahead, while calling on the U.S. to withdraw the threat [bbc.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1]. The warning comes after Beijing suddenly imposed strict export controls on critical raw materials, a move that preceded the tariff threat and has reignited tensions between the world’s two largest economies [washingtonpost.com#1]. Amid the tough rhetoric, the President urged Beijing to be less confrontational, and Chinese officials publicly pressed for the withdrawal of the tariff plan, signaling that political messaging is continuing alongside economic measures [japantoday.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/SZSEZB1ewkHYlk2QYBYt0eckvrLNyCb1x2gAVdPQvk4XZZCEYSKWS8KPSl_guRGWQdRCBsQHh8iLw8RBJ4gB7j2qZwqpX-QLNeDyE8qU715CbOxnLHCGBerpkxS-8iaWh5S5l_ByBO3-BzmwyMWgYT5kXww' alt='China says it will stand firm as the US threatens a 100% tariff on Chinese imports.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tariff threat: President Trump has threatened an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports, escalating trade tensions [washingtonpost.com#1][bbc.com#1].</li><li>China’s stance: Beijing vowed to stand firm and warned of potential countermeasures if the tariff is imposed, while urging the U.S. to withdraw the threat [abcnews.go.com#1][japantoday.com#1][bbc.com#1].</li><li>Trigger context: The U.S. tariff threat followed China’s sudden imposition of strict export controls on critical raw materials [washingtonpost.com#1].</li><li>Rhetorical signals: China accused the U.S. of &quot;double standards,&quot; and the President urged Beijing to be less confrontational [bbc.com#1][japantoday.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Chinese government: China says it will stand firm, could introduce countermeasures, and calls on the U.S. to withdraw the 100% tariff threat. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cn828kg8rmzo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>United States (President Trump): The President threatened an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports after Beijing’s export controls and urged Beijing to be less confrontational. (<a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/china-vows-to-stand-firm-against-trump%27s-tariff-threat.-he-urges-beijing-to-be-less-confrontational'>Japan Today</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/12/trump-tariff-threat-china-retaliation/'>China vows to retaliate if Trump makes good on 100 percent tariff threat</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/china-shows-sign-backing-issuing-call-us-withdraw-126464972'>China won&#x27;t backing down while issuing call for US to withdraw tariff threat</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/china-vows-to-stand-firm-against-trump%27s-tariff-threat.-he-urges-beijing-to-be-less-confrontational'>China vows to stand firm against Trump&#x27;s tariff threat</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cn828kg8rmzo'>China accuses US of &#x27;double standards&#x27; over tariff threat</a> - bbc.com</li></ul>